L = \lim_{x \to a} \frac{f(x) - f(a)}{x - a} = \lim_{c_x \to a} f'(c_x)
\lim_{x \to a} \frac{f(x) - f(a)}{x - a} = f'(a)
\lim_{c_x \to a} f'(c_x) = f'(a)
0 < |c_x - a| < \delta \Longrightarrow |f'(c_x) - L| < \epsilon
0 < |x - a| < \delta \Longrightarrow |c_x - a| < \delta
0 < |x - a| < \delta \Longrightarrow |f'(c_x) - L| < \epsilon
\frac{f(x) - f(a)}{x - a} = f'(c_x) \text { for all } x
